<h1 id="adding-labels">Adding Labels</h1>

<p>Now we are going to add a label to Broad St. Pump so the map reader can identify it.  Follow the steps as outlined and refer to the video below.</p>

<p><strong class="label label-green">1)</strong> Right click on Broad St. Pump and click Label.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Note a label appears next to the point but it isn’t very easy to read.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong class="label label-green">2)</strong> Right click on Broad St. Pump again and click Labeling Properties, change the font size and add a halo to make the label easier to read.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Halos can make your text stand out against a background.  Increasing the font size also helps the text stand out.</li>
  <li>You can change many other aspects of the label text.  Play around with the properties to see what happens when you make changes.  Hit apply after each change.</li>
</ul>

